cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new scheme for increasing the throughput of video files in cellular communications systems. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with video files and their transmission. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper proposes a distributed caching scheme for video files. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper exploits the redundancy of user requests and uses device-to-device localized transmissions. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible category as the paper analyzes the optimal collaboration distance and the trade-off between frequency reuse and finding a requested file within the collaboration distance.
